summary: <t> Students from the University of Surrey discovered thousands of colonies . </t> <t> They submerged coins and notes in agar to accelerate growth pf bacteria . </t> <t> Most were harmless on the money , but one caused boils and spots . </t> <t> Previous studies have revealed MRSA bacteria on notes and coins . </t>
summary_trees:
# ::snt  Students from the University of Surrey discovered thousands of colonies . 
(d / discover-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (s / study-01)
            :source (u / university
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "University"
                        :op2 "of"
                        :op3 "Surrey")))
      :ARG1 (c / colony
            :quant (m / multiple
                  :op1 1000)))

# ::snt  They submerged coins and notes in agar to accelerate growth pf bacteria . 
(s / submerge-01
      :ARG0 (t / they)
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (c / coin)
            :op2 (n / note))
      :ARG2 (a2 / agar)
      :purpose (a3 / accelerate-01
            :ARG0 t
            :ARG1 (g / grow-03
                  :ARG1 (b / bacterium
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Pf")))))

# ::snt  Most were harmless on the money , but one caused boils and spots . 
(c / contrast-01
      :ARG1 (h / harmful-02
            :polarity -
            :ARG0 (m / most)
            :mod (o / on-the-money))
      :ARG2 (c2 / cause-01
            :ARG0 (o2 / one)
            :ARG1 (a / and
                  :op1 (b / boil-01)
                  :op2 (s / spot))))

# ::snt  Previous studies have revealed MRSA bacteria on notes and coins . 
(r / reveal-01
      :ARG0 (s / study-01
            :time (p / previous))
      :ARG1 (b / bacterium
            :mod (d / disease
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "MRSA"))
            :location (a / and
                  :op1 (n2 / note)
                  :op2 (c / coin))))
